Search for a NUL character in a string:

Copy
let str = "Visit Demo2s.com.\0Learn JavaScript.";
let patt1 = /\0/;
let result = str.search(patt1);
console.log(result);
Output:


Description
The \0 metacharacter is used to find NUL character.

\0 returns the position where the NUL character was found.

If no match is found, it returns -1.

Browser Compatibility
Chrome.png	Node.png	Firefox.png	Safari.png	Edge.png	Opera.png
\0	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes
Syntax
Copy
new RegExp("\\0") or simply: /\0/
